<TITLE> Man killed in Bagherat 'due to land dispute' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Bagerhat, Apr 28 (bdnews24.com)  A land dispute is alleged to have resulted in a man's death in Bagerhat on Wednesday. Police recovered the body in the morning and sent it to Bagerhat General Hospital for autopsy. The victim was identified as Tafazzal Hossain Tofa, 50, son of Nur Mohammad Shikdar of Sonakandar village in Gajaria union. Police arrested his wife Rawsan Ara for her alleged involvement in the murder case. Tofa was killed at his in-laws house at Vasa village under Dhopakhali union, police said. Kasua thana police chief Khairul Anam told bdnews24.com that Tofa used to stay with his father-in-law Abdul Gafur Shikdar after the marriage. Anam said that it was suspected that the murder happened as a result of a land dispute. His wife was arrested to question her in this concern. Rawsan, however, told reporters that she had gone to the wash room at around 3am and when she returned she found her husband lying in the bed in a pool of blood. bdnews24.
